## Icon transitions (home page standard)

**Always use the same icon hover transition as the home page across the whole project.** Check and obey this in every component that shows an icon inside a card or clickable area. Icon transition should be like home page.

### Standard pattern

1. **Parent** must have `group` so the icon responds to hover.
2. **Icon wrapper** (the circle/box around the icon):
   - `inline-flex h-14 w-14 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-primary/10 text-primary transition-all duration-300 group-hover:bg-primary group-hover:text-primary-foreground`
   - Optional: use `rounded-2xl` instead of `rounded-full` where the design uses rounded squares.
3. **Icon** (the Lucide/Remix component):
   - `h-6 w-6 transition-transform duration-300 group-hover:scale-110 group-hover:[transform:rotateY(180deg)]`
   - So on hover: icon scales up slightly and flips on the Y axis (3D flip).

### Reference components

- `components/frontend/common/feature-card.tsx` (canonical)
- Home hero stats: `components/frontend/home/homepage-hero-section.tsx` (icon flip: `group-hover:scale-x-[-1]` variant)
- Home modules: `components/frontend/home/mlm-software-modules.tsx` (rotateY(180deg))

When adding or editing any section that displays icons in cards (e.g. about-company, modules, features, services), always apply this icon transition pattern unless the design explicitly requires a different effect.

